40|$|TV {{signals are}} carried towards {{end-users}} using different (<b>broadcast)</b> <b>technologies</b> and by different providers. This is causing {{differences in the}} playout timing of the TV signal at different locations and devices. Authors have developed a measurement system for measuring the relative playout delay of a TV output. This measurement system consists of an application running on Android and a back-end system, and uses the Gracenote fingerprinting platform...|$|R
40|$|The {{increasing}} number of services with a mass interest and the parallel increasing demand for service quality, is paving the way to research studies on how to deliver a multicast content with end-to-end QoS guarantees. This paper gives an analysis of NGN QoS frameworks, multicast and <b>broadcast</b> <b>technologies</b> and their possible interactions. In this respect, this paper describes an innovative inter-domain QoS-aware multicast protocol...|$|R
40|$|The optimal {{allocation}} of the retransmission bandwidth {{is essential for}} IPTV service providers to ensure maximal service quality. This paper highlights {{the relevance of the}} wireless transport in today’s IPTV solution and discusses how this new media affects the existing <b>broadcast</b> <b>technologies.</b> A new Markovian channel model is developed to address the optimization issues of the retransmission throughput, and a new method is presented which is evaluated by empirical measurements followed by mathematical analysis...|$|R
