40|$|WLAN {{and other}} radio <b>broadcast</b> <b>technologies</b> are now commonplace. However, the {{widespread}} usage of these technologies {{comes at the}} price of loss of location privacy. Although a number of network-level solutions exist to lessen the problem, we describe an improved approach to location privacy at the link layer. We present a generic mechanism and then map it to the common IEEE 802. 11 protocol set. The article finally provides an analysis of our mechanism in terms of privacy and performance...|$|R
